Otto's pizza by the slice is a great place to drop by for a snack or a few slices of pizza.  Centrally located in Harvard Square, this place always has some interesting combinations to try including things like: meatloaf, mashed potato, and onion pizza.  It's a tiny location with basically only a pick up counter and a small bench for standing to eat your slice.  During the summer they do have a few tables they put out as well.  So plan accordingly.  If you're craving some think crust pizza with a slew of interesting topping combinations, give Otto's a try.  You won't be disappointed.

The Harvard Square location for Otto pizza is very small, and is essentially take out only. That being said they have the pizza game down to a science and quickly usher guests in and out of the very small store front. Most people are grabbing slices which they display behind the register and will heat up when ordered. When I have ordered a full pie they typically have it ready within 15 minutes. They have the best gluten free crust around, and do a pretty good job not to cross contaminate the food. This location recently added an outdoor seating area on the sidewalk that has bout 5 tables to eat at when the weather is nicer.

Toppings are creative, and include options such as mashed potato, bacon, and scallion, butternut squash, ricotta, and cranberry, and more.  They always have at least 10 of the ever rotating slices to choose from, and they're guaranteed not to disappoint.  The only drawback: seating is very limited, so plan to take your slice to go.
